1	✅ Full Self-Contained Design + Skeleton Code
2	Here is a complete, standalone design and Rust skeleton for gha-isolated — a wrapper CLI around gha-outrunner that gives you unified, reliable, VM-preferring GitHub Actions runners across macOS, Linux, and GCE.
3	
4	1. Project Overview
5	Tool Name: gha-isolated
6	Purpose: Provide a single, easy-to-use CLI that runs self-hosted GitHub Actions runners with the strongest practical isolation available on the current platform, while keeping operational overhead low.
7	Core Principles
8		•	Prefer VM-level isolation when possible (Tart on macOS, libvirt on Linux).
9		•	Fall back gracefully to container isolation with hard resource limits.
10		•	Use GitHub Scale Sets + ephemeral runners by default.
11		•	Apply consistent resource protection everywhere.
12		•	Work the same way on a developer laptop and inside a GCE VM.
13	Supported Platforms (v1 target)
14		•	macOS (Apple Silicon) → Tart backend (VMs)
15		•	Linux with KVM → libvirt backend (VMs)
16		•	Linux / GCE (no strong KVM) → Docker + Sysbox (with strict limits)
17		•	GCE → Same as Linux (run inside a GCE VM)
18	
19	2. High-Level Architecture
20	gha-isolated (Rust binary)
21	├── CLI (clap)
22	├── Platform Detection
23	├── Backend Selection (Tart / libvirt / Docker+Sysbox)
24	├── Config Generation (outrunner.yml + resource limits)
25	├── Runner Lifecycle (start/stop/status via gha-outrunner)
26	├── Service Management (systemd / launchd)
27	└── Optional GCE helpers
28	Data Flow (start command)
29		1	Detect platform + capabilities
30		2	Choose best backend
31		3	Generate/validate outrunner.yml with resource limits
32		4	Ensure prerequisites (gha-outrunner binary, Sysbox/Tart, etc.)
33		5	Start gha-outrunner with correct flags/backend
34	
